%N A393235 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of ordered rooted trees with node weights summing to n that have k non-root nodes; such that the root has weight 0, non-root nodes have positive integer weights, and no two adjacent sibling nodes have the same weight.
%F A393235 G.f.: C(x,y) satisfies C(x,y) = 1/(1 - y*C(x,y) * Sum_{k>0} (x^k/(1 + x^k*y*C(x,y)))).
